# PUBLISHING Domain Rules
# =======================
# Version management, npm releases, and git tagging for see-my-clicks.

PUBLISHING_RULE_0=Use alpha versioning during development: next unreleased version with -alpha.N suffix, increment build number on each push
PUBLISHING_RULE_1=Follow semver strictly: patch=bug fixes only, minor=new features/UI/behavior, major=breaking plugin API or config changes
PUBLISHING_RULE_2=If alpha series started as patch but new features were added, bump to next minor for stable release
PUBLISHING_RULE_3=NEVER push or publish unless user explicitly says "push", "release", or similar - commit locally only
PUBLISHING_RULE_4=Alpha publishes automatically on push to main via GitHub Actions (--tag alpha dist-tag)
PUBLISHING_RULE_5=Stable release: drop alpha suffix, commit, git tag v{version}, push tag - triggers publish with latest dist-tag
PUBLISHING_RULE_6=Authentication uses npm Trusted Publishing (OIDC) - no npm tokens needed
PUBLISHING_RULE_7=Check current version in package.json before bumping - never guess the version number
